    "narrative": "For the April 19th slate, **Will Smith** (73.95) and **Tyler Freeman** (71.80) lead the charge for LawDog. **Will Smith** benefits from a high-floor matchup against Lorenzen, with park factors and a projected #3 spot padding his efficiency. However, the standout play is **Tyler Freeman**, whose massive +19% SP skill boost against a favorable 5.52 xERA from Roki Sasaki makes him our premier outfield option. **Jonathan Aranda** (67.96) is also a mandatory start, as he draws a strong platoon advantage against Keller, with favorable wind conditions pushing his profile into the high 60s. We are banking on this trio to anchor our counting stats while the rest of the lineup provides steady support.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involves **Matt Chapman**, who fell just short of our lineup threshold with a 52.85 rating. While his park environment against Poulin is positive, his projected efficiency simply could not overcome the higher-ranked starts of **Daulton Varsho** (66.97) and **Bryson Stott** (64.41), both of whom are buoyed by significantly better platoon splits. Elsewhere, we must navigate risk: **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez** are facing the elite arm of Garrett Crochet; the -19% SP skill penalty suppresses their scores, making **Wenceel Perez** (45.86) our most volatile asset today. We are monitoring lineup confirmations for **Will Smith**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Bryson Stott**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Lawrence Butler**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Cal Raleigh** closely; any downward shift in their expected batting order will necessitate a reassessment of our daily cap utilization.",
